'''吉尔·特蕾西·拜登'''（{{lang-en|Jill Tracy Biden}}，{{bd|1951年|6月3日}}），婚前原姓'''雅各布斯'''（Jacobs），曾用姓'''史蒂文森'''（Stevenson），是一位[[美国|美国]][[教师|教师]]，現任[[美国第一夫人|美国第一夫人]]，即美国現任（第46任）[[美国总统|总统]][[乔·拜登|乔·拜登]]之妻子。吉尔·拜登生于[[新泽西州|新泽西州]][[大西洋县|大西洋县]]的{{link-en|哈默顿 (新泽西州)|Hammonton, New Jersey|哈默顿}}，在[[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]][[蒙哥马利县_(宾夕法尼亚州)|蒙哥马利县]]的{{link-en|柳林 (宾夕法尼亚州)|Willow Grove, Pennsylvania|柳林}}长大。她和乔·拜登于1977年结婚。乔·拜登在此前还有一段婚姻，并育有二子一女，但其前妻和小女儿因交通事故丧生。吉尔与乔结婚后，成为他两个儿子[[博·拜登|博]]和[[亨特·拜登|亨特]]的继母。乔与吉尔二人于1981年诞下一個女兒[[阿什莉·拜登|阿什莉]]。

吉尔在[[特拉华大学|特拉华大学]]获得学士学位，在{{link-en|宾夕法尼亚州西切斯特大学|West Chester University of Pennsylvania|西切斯特大学}}和[[维拉诺瓦大学|维拉诺瓦大学]]获得硕士学位，随后又在特拉华大学获得博士学位。她担任了13年的高中英文和阅读教师，还在一家精神病医院为患有情感障碍的青少年辅导课程。1993年至2008年期间，她在{{link-en|特拉华理工社区学院|Delaware Technical Community College}}担任英文和写作辅导员。2009年起，她开始在{{link-en|北弗吉尼亚社区学院|Northern Virginia Community College}}担任英文教授，并成为首位在丈夫任职副总统期间仍保留自己有薪水的工作的[[美國副總統配偶|美国第二夫人]]。她还创建了非营利组织“拜登乳腺健康倡议行动”（{{lang|en|Biden Breast Health Initiative}}），也是“图书伙伴”（{{lang|en|Book Buddies}}）项目的联合创始人之一。她还积极参与了旨在帮助军人家庭的非营利组织“Delaware Boots on the Ground”的活动。

==早年生活==
吉尔·特蕾西·雅各布斯于1951年6月3日出生于新泽西州大西洋县的哈默顿。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/drbiden/status/341641863222161408 |title=RT @whitehouse Happy birthday, @DrBiden! - Take note @Wikipedia! |publisher=The White House/[[Twitter|Twitter]] |date=2013-06-03 |accessdate=2014-02-10 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304234329/https://twitter.com/drbiden/status/341641863222161408 |dead-url=no }} The date of June 5 given in [http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/documents/Meet_The_Bidens.html this 2009 ''Washington Post'' piece] {{Wayback|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/documents/Meet_The_Bidens.html |date=20201015143531 }} previously used in this article is incorrect.</ref><ref name="pi082708" />她有四个妹妹，五个孩子在儿童时期随父亲的工作变化而多次搬家，童年的大部分时光都是在宾夕法尼亚州蒙哥马利县的柳林度过的。<ref name="tnj100608" /><ref name="progressohio.org">{{cite web |url=http://www.progressohio.org/page/community/post/daveharding/CHBm |title=Meet Dr. Jill Biden |accessdate=2009-02-27 |publisher=Progress Ohio.org |archivedate=2009-02-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090227221637/http://www.progressohio.org/page/community/post/daveharding/CHBm }}</ref>吉尔的父亲唐纳德·C·雅各布斯（{{lang|en|Donald C. Jacobs}}，1927–1999）<ref name="pi060999"/>是一名银行职员，后来成为宾夕法尼亚州{{link-en|栗树山 (宾夕法尼亚州)|Chestnut Hill, Pennsylvania|栗树山}}一家{{link-en|储蓄贷款协会|Savings and loan association}}的负责人。<ref name="vogue1108">{{cite magazine |url=http://www.vogue.com/magazine/article/jill-bidenbrall-the-vice-presidents-women/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221164344/http://www.vogue.com/magazine/article/jill-bidenbrall-the-vice-presidents-women/ |archivedate=2014-02-21 |title=All the Vice-President's Women |author=Van Meter, Jonathan |magazine=Vogue |date=2008-11 |accessdate=2010-11-08 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>雅各布斯一家最早来自意大利，原姓吉亚科帕（{{lang|en|Giacoppa}}），后来吉尔的祖父将这个姓氏英文化，改成了雅各布斯（{{lang|en|Jacobs}}）。<ref name="vogue1108"/><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/05/31/AR2009053102568.html | title=Obamas' Chow: Politically Palatable | author=Argetsinger, Amy and Roberts, Roxanne | newspaper=The Washington Post | date=2009-06-01 | accessdate=2009-06-01 | archive-date=2020-10-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201013110201/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/05/31/AR2009053102568.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>吉尔的母亲邦妮·珍·高福瑞·雅各布斯（{{lang|en|Bonny Jean Godfrey Jacobs}}，1930–2008）<ref name="tnj100608">{{cite news | url=http://search.delawareonline.com/sp?skin=100&aff=1117&keywords=Joe+Biden%27s+mother-in-law+dies+at+78&pubDate=180&author= | title=Joe Biden's mother-in-law dies at 78 | author=Nathans, Aaron | newspaper=The News Journal | date=2008-10-06 | accessdate=2009-02-04 | format=fee required | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223093238/http://search.delawareonline.com/sp?skin=100&aff=1117&keywords=Joe+Biden's+mother-in-law+dies+at+78&pubDate=180&author= | archivedate=2014-02-23 }}</ref>则是一位[[家庭主妇|家庭主妇]]。<ref name="pi060999">{{cite news | url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=PI&s_site=philly&p_multi=PI&p_theme=realcities&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB5CE453393F8F9&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM | title=Donald C. Jacobs, 72 | newspaper=The Philadelphia Inquirer | date=1999-06-09 | accessdate=2008-09-19 | archive-date=2020-11-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106102217/http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=PI&s_site=philly&p_multi=PI&p_theme=realcities&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB5CE453393F8F9&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date%3AD&s_trackval=GooglePM | dead-url=no }}</ref>
雅各布斯一家的宗教氛围并不算浓厚，但吉尔在九年级时却萌生了希望加入教会的想法，并自己独立参加了[[长老宗|长老宗]]的相关培训。<ref name="vogue1108"/>

吉尔一直希望能拥有“自己的钱、自己的身份和自己的事业”，<ref name="nyt082508"/>15岁便开始了自己的第一份工作。<ref name="vogue1108"/><ref name="nyt082508">{{cite news | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/25/us/politics/25wife.html | title=Jill Biden Heads Toward Life in the Spotlight | author=Seelye, Katharine Q. | newspaper=The New York Times | date=2008-08-24 | accessdate=2008-08-25 | archive-date=2008-12-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081210193454/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/08/25/us/politics/25wife.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>她在{{link-en|上莫兰德高中|Upper Moreland High School}}完成高中学业，期间社交广泛而且行为颇为叛逆，然而对英文课却始终情有独钟。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.phillyburbs.com/pb-dyn/news/113-11072008-1617762.html | title=Jill Biden getting attention | author=Tasker, Annie | newspaper=Bucks County Courier Times | date=2008-11-07 | accessdate=2008-11-07 | archiveurl=https://archive.is/20090217190731/http://phillyburbs.com/pb-dyn/news/113-11072008-1617762.html | archivedate=2009-02-17 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>1969年，吉尔从高中毕业。<ref name="bcct082808">{{cite news |url=http://www.phillyburbs.com/pb-dyn/news/111-08282008-1582679.html |title=Upper Moreland grad Jill Biden in campaign limelight |author=Cosentino, Dom |newspaper=Bucks County Courier Times |date=2008-08-28 |accessdate=2008-08-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080901170350/http://www.phillyburbs.com/pb-dyn/news/111-08282008-1582679.html |archivedate=2008-09-01 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

==教育和事业经历，婚姻与家庭==
吉尔后来进入[[短期大学|初级学院]]学习時裝營銷，然而她很快便发现这一专业并不尽如人意。<ref name="vogue1108" />1970年2月，她与比尔·史蒂文森（{{lang|en|Bill Stevenson}}）结婚。史蒂文森曾经是大学的[[美式足球|美式足球]]队员，<ref name="udr-stevenson">{{cite news |url=http://www.udreview.com/2.1980/behind-the-stone-balloon-1.142251 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221100855/http://www.udreview.com/2.1980/behind-the-stone-balloon-1.142251 |archivedate=2014-02-21 |title=Behind the Stone Balloon: Part 1 |author=Markovetz, Jessie |newspaper=The Review |location=University of Delaware |date=2006-11-21 |accessdate=2010-07-28 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>数年之后在[[特拉华州|特拉华州]][[纽瓦克_(特拉华州)|纽瓦克]]的[[特拉华大学|特拉华大学]]附近开了一家酒吧“Stone Ballon”。<ref name="udr-stevenson"/>这家酒吧后来成为全美国最成功的大学酒吧之一。<ref name="udr-stevenson" />  

吉尔之后进入特拉华大学，主修英文专业。<ref name="vogue1108"/>之后她休假一年，为[[威尔明顿_(特拉华州)|威尔明顿]]当地的一家公司做[[模特|模特]]。<ref name="vogue1108"/><ref name="udr-stevenson"/>然而此时，她与史蒂文森的感情已经日渐疏远。<ref name="udr-stevenson" /> 

1975年3月，吉尔重新回到大学校园，遇到了比她年长的[[乔·拜登|乔·拜登]]。<ref name="nyt082508"/>二人是在拜登的兄弟介绍的相亲中认识的，在此之前乔·拜登已经在当地的广告中见过吉尔的照片。<ref name="nyt082508"/>同年，吉尔从特拉华大学毕业获得[[文学士|文学士]]学位，<ref name="dtcc">{{cite web|url=http://www.dtcc.edu/catalog/pdf/personnel.pdf|title=Administrative, Instructional, and Student Services Personnel|accessdate=2008-08-23|publisher=Delaware Technical & Community College|archive-date=2009-12-01|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5lhMSa0qe?url=http://www.dtcc.edu/catalog/pdf/personnel.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.udel.edu/udaily/2009/nov/election110508.html | title=University of Delaware plays major role in national election | author=Thomas, Neil | publisher=University of Delaware | date=2008-11-05 | accessdate=2009-01-24 | archive-date=2020-06-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605040946/http://www1.udel.edu/udaily/2009/nov/election110508.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>开始担任高中英文教师。<ref name="nyt082508" />与此同时，她还在处理与史蒂文森错综复杂的离婚案。1976年，二人离婚案完成最终判决。吉尔要求在离婚时获得“Stone Ballon”的一半股份，但判决结果并未如她所愿。<ref name="udr-stevenson" />

吉尔和乔·拜登于1977年6月17日结婚，婚礼在[[纽约市|纽约市]][[联合国总部大楼|联合国总部]]的教堂举行，<ref name="pi082708"/><ref name="nyt082508"/>此时距乔·拜登首任妻子和幼女在交通事故中逝世已经过去四年半的时间。<ref name="pi082708"/>乔·拜登曾数次向吉尔求婚，然而吉尔始终犹豫不决，她担心自己能否做出承诺将乔和前妻在交通事故中幸存的两个儿子抚养长大。<ref name="vogue1108"/>在乔第五次求婚时，吉尔才最终下定决心。<ref name="vogue1108"/>婚后她和两个继子的关系发展迅速，两兄弟很快就接受了这个新的母亲，甚至不把她当作继母看待，直接叫她“妈妈”。<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/book-party/wp/2015/06/04/from-jill-to-mom-inside-jill-bidens-relationship-with-beau-and-hunter/|title = From ‘Jill’ to ‘Mom’ — inside Jill Biden’s relationship with Beau and Hunter|accessdate = 2016-01-22|author = |date = 2015-06-04|publisher = The Washington Post|last = Lozada|first = Carlos|archive-date = 2016-01-31|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160131014752/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/book-party/wp/2015/06/04/from-jill-to-mom-inside-jill-bidens-relationship-with-beau-and-hunter/|dead-url = no}}</ref>她在婚后继续自己的教育事业。1981年，她在怀孕期间获得了{{link-en|宾夕法尼亚州西切斯特大学|West Chester University of Pennsylvania|西切斯特大学}}的[[教育硕士|教育硕士]]学位。<ref name="vogue1108"/><ref name="dtcc"/><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.wcuquad.com/102570/uncategorized/the-quad-talks-with-jill-biden/ | title=The Quad talks with Jill Biden | author=Stern, Frank | publisher=''The Quad'' | date=2008-10-20 | accessdate=2008-12-29 | archive-date=2020-11-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113072436/https://wcuquad.com/102570/uncategorized/the-quad-talks-with-jill-biden/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>1981年6月8日，吉尔产下女儿[[阿什莉·拜登|阿什莉·拜登]]，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/fullpage?id=5659057 |title=Joe and Jill Welcome Ashley |publisher=ABC |accessdate=2014-02-07 |archive-date=2014-02-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223225114/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/fullpage?id=5659057 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Katherine Thomson |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/03/29/ashley-biden-pictures-pho_n_180464.html |title=Ashley Biden Pictures (PHOTOS) |publisher=Huffington Post |date=2009-03-29 |accessdate=2014-02-14 |archive-date=2017-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307143852/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2009/03/29/ashley-biden-pictures-pho_n_180464.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>随后为抚养三个子女暂停了自己的事业。<ref name="nj031907">{{cite news | url=http://search.delawareonline.com/sp?skin=100&aff=1117&keywords=%22It%20was%20Joe,%20the%20boys,%20and%20the%20state%20of%20Delaware%22 | title=Determined to stay in school | author=Hale, Charlotte | newspaper=The News Journal | date=2007-03-19 | accessdate=2008-08-29 | subscription=yes | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080901212036/http://search.delawareonline.com/sp?skin=100&aff=1117&keywords=%22It%20was%20Joe,%20the%20boys,%20and%20the%20state%20of%20Delaware%22 | archivedate=2008-09-01 }}</ref>

两年后，吉尔重新回到工作当中，继续担任英文教师。<ref name="nyt082508" />1980年代，她在罗克福德中心[[精神病医院|精神病医院]]为患有[[情感障碍|情感障碍]]的青少年担任了五年的历史教师。<ref name="pi082708" /><ref name="vogue1108" />1987年，吉尔在[[维拉诺瓦大学|维拉诺瓦大学]]获得英文专业的[[文学硕士|文学硕士]]学位，这也是她的第二个[[硕士|硕士]]学位。<ref name="pi082708">{{cite news |url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20080827_Colleagues_see_a_caring__giving_Jill_Biden.html |title=Colleagues see a caring, giving Jill Biden |author=Farrell, Joelle |newspaper=The Philadelphia Inquirer |date=2008-08-27 |accessdate=2008-08-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080901030119/http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20080827_Colleagues_see_a_caring__giving_Jill_Biden.html |archivedate=2008-09-01 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="dtcc"/>在其夫乔·拜登参加[[1988年美国总统选举|1988年总统选举]]的民主党内初选时，她表示自己如果最终成为[[美国第一夫人|第一夫人]]也会坚持继续为这些情感障碍的儿童担任教师。<ref name="caroli">{{cite book | last=Caroli | first=Betty Boyd | title=First Ladies: From Martha Washington to Laura Bush | publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2003 | isbn=0-19-516676-0 | page=297}}</ref>她在公立高中任教时间总计长达13年。<ref name="nyt082508" /><ref name="vogue1108" />

1993年到2008年期间，吉尔在{{link-en|特拉华理工社区学院|Delaware Technical Community College}}[[斯坦顿_(特拉华州)|斯坦顿]]/[[威尔明顿_(特拉华州)|威尔明顿]]校区担任辅导员，<ref name="dtcc"/><ref name="wapo-cc"/><ref name="npr010108"/>教授英文并辅导写作，她的教学重点是为学生提高自信心。<ref name="wapo-cc"/><ref name="lat082708">{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2008/aug/27/nation/na-jill27 |title=Jill Biden has a low-key appeal |author=Gaouette, Nicole |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=2008-08-27 |accessdate=2014-02-14 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121215175204/http://articles.latimes.com/2008/aug/27/nation/na-jill27 |archivedate=2012-12-15 }}</ref>她曾这样形容自己在[[社区学院|社区学院]]的教学工作：“我感觉我能让他们的人生发生更大的变化。我热爱这些学生们。在这里，我感觉很放松很舒适。这些女性为了获得学位重新回到学校学习，我热爱她们，因为她们是那么的专注、努力。”<ref name="wapo-cc">{{cite news | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/22/AR2008102203657.html | title=Campaign Curriculum | author=Copeland, Libby | newspaper=The Washington Post | date=2008-10-23 | accessdate=2014-02-14 | archive-date=2020-06-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605041058/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/10/22/AR2008102203657.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

吉尔还是“拜登乳腺健康倡议行动”（{{lang|en|"Biden Breast Health Initiative"}}）的创始人。这个非营利组织成立于1993年，旨在为特拉华州的学校、社区及其他团体免费提供乳腺健康的教育和宣传项目。<ref>{{cite news |first=Nancy |last=Churnin |title=Obama's VP pick, Joe Biden, could heighten breast cancer awareness |url=http://fitnessblog.dallasnews.com/archives/2008/08/expect-more-breast-cancer-awar.html |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120711194506/http://fitnessblog.dallasnews.com/archives/2008/08/expect-more-breast-cancer-awar.html |archivedate=2012-07-11 |work=The Dallas Morning News |date=2008-08-23 |accessdate=2008-08-23 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://bbhi4health.org/people.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222173142/http://bbhi4health.org/people.html |archivedate=2014-02-22 |title=About Us |publisher=Biden Breast Health Initiative |accessdate=2014-02-07 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>这一组织在成立之后的15年内为超过7,000位高中女生普及了乳腺健康的知识。<ref name="wh-bio" />2007年，吉尔协助成立了“Book Buddies”组织，这一组织的目标是为低收入家庭儿童提供免费图书。<ref name="wh-bio"/>她还积极参与了旨在帮助军人家庭的非营利组织“Delaware Boots on the Ground”的活动。<ref name="lat082708"/>她还曾参加公益性的{{link-en|海军陆战队马拉松|Marine Corps Marathon}}，推广社区健身运动。<ref name="nyt082508" />

吉尔之后又以“吉尔·雅各布斯”的身份回到学校攻读博士学位。<ref name="nj031907" />2007年1月，吉尔在55岁时获得了特拉华大学教育领导学专业的[[教育博士|教育博士]]学位。<ref name="pi082708" /><ref name="wh-bio">{{cite web |url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/administration/jill_biden/ |title=Dr. Jill Biden |publisher=The White House |accessdate=2009-01-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090122062141/http://www.whitehouse.gov/administration/jill_biden/ |archivedate=2009-01-22 }}</ref><ref name="dissert" /><ref name="lat020209" />她的学位论文则是以“吉尔·雅各布斯-拜登”的身份发表的。<ref name="dissert">{{cite book | last=Jacobs-Biden | first=Jill | title=Student Retention at the Community College: Meeting Students' Needs | publisher=University of Delaware | year=2006 | url=http://proquest.umi.com/pqdlink?did=1251897961&Fmt=7&clientId=79356&RQT=309&VName=PQD&cfc=1e=PQD&cfc=1 | subscription=yes | access-date=2014-02-10 | archive-date=2009-06-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090623000232/http://proquest.umi.com/pqdlink?did=1251897961&Fmt=7&clientId=79356&RQT=309&VName=PQD&cfc=1e=PQD&cfc=1 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

==2008年总统选举==
[[File:Obamas_and_Bidens.jpg|thumb]]宣布乔·拜登为自己的竞选搭档。图为宣布现场照片，左起依次为贝拉克·奥巴马、[[米歇尔·奥巴马|米歇尔·奥巴马]]、吉尔·拜登和乔·拜登。]]
[[乔治·沃克·布什|乔治·沃克·布什]]在[[2004年美国总统选举|2004年总统选举]]中成功连任后，吉尔便鼓动丈夫参选下一任总统。<ref name="npr010108"/>之后她对此表示：“我当时真的连续一周都身穿（哀伤的）黑色。我认为在当时美国的一切已经足够糟了，所以我完全无法相信他竟然能连任成功。我坚决反对[[伊拉克战争|那场战争]]。之后我对乔说，‘你一定要改变这个局面，你必须去改变现状。’”<ref name="wapo-cc"/>在[[2008年美国总统选举|2008年]]乔·拜登参加民主党内初选期间，她在工作日依然继续自己的教师工作，而在周末与丈夫一同参加竞选活动。<ref name="npr010108"/>她表示，如果自己成为第一夫人，关注的重点仍然是教育问题。<ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://content.time.com/time/specials/2007/article/0,28804,1660946_1661078,00.html | title=Democrat Candidate Spouses: Jill Biden | magazine=Time | accessdate=2014-02-14 | date=2007-09-13 | archive-date=2020-11-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106102402/http://content.time.com/time/specials/2007/article/0,28804,1660946_1661078,00.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>她还表示自己无意参与政治，并不打算在内阁中寻求职位。<ref name="npr010108">{{cite news | url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=17764989 | title=Presidential Candidates' Spouses: Jill Biden | author=Norris, Michelle | work=All Things Considered | publisher=NPR | date=2008-01-01 | accessdate=2008-08-26 | archive-date=2020-06-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200608143727/https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=17764989 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

2008年1月，乔·拜登退出党内初选。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.delawareonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080104/NEWS/801040354 |title=Biden ends his long-shot run |publisher=Delaware Online |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080108035224/http://www.delawareonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20080104%2FNEWS%2F801040354 |archivedate=2008-01-08 |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2017-06-08 }}</ref>而在同年8月，在丈夫乔·拜登成为民主党候选人[[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]的参选搭档之后，吉尔又重新开始参加竞选活动。她在竞选活动中佩戴了一枚{{link-en|蓝星母亲|Blue Star Mothers Club}}徽章（军人母亲的象征），以表示其子[[博·拜登|博·拜登]]曾在伊拉克服役的经历。<ref name="wapo-cc"/>吉尔并不是一位老练的政治演说家，但是她擅长与听众建立情感上的联系和共鸣。<ref name="wapo-cc"/>她还在竞选期间与[[米歇尔·奥巴马|米歇尔·奥巴马]]共同出席了一系列活动。<ref name="pol112708">{{cite news |url=http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1108/16040.html |title=Jill Biden: Untraditional, unapologetic |author=Lee, Carol E. |newspaper=The Politico |date=2008-11-27 |accessdate=2008-11-28 |archive-date=2008-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081129023704/http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1108/16040.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>此时正值2008年秋季学期，此时吉尔仍然继续在特拉华理工社区学院任教，竞选活动期间仍每周工作四天。在周末的竞选活动中，她会在竞选宣传车上批阅学生试卷和作业。<ref name="tnj100608" /><ref name="wapo-cc" /><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.reuters.com/article/joeBiden/idUSN0143167020081103 | title=Jill Biden, teacher who avoids 'Washington scene' | author=Pleming, Sue | agency=Reuters | date=2008-11-03 | accessdate=2008-11-06 | archive-date=2009-01-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090120175135/http://www.reuters.com/article/joeBiden/idUSN0143167020081103 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

==第二夫人==
=== 第一任期 ===
[[File:20090120_Jill_and_Joe_Biden_at_Homestates_Ball.JPG|thumb]]舞会上]]
[[File:Jill_Biden_official_portrait.jpg|thumb]]
成为[[美國副總統配偶|美国第二夫人]]后，吉尔随丈夫搬到位于[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿特区]][[美国海军天文台|美国海军天文台]]的[[天文台环路一号|天文台环路一号]]副总统官邸居住。她不愿放弃教师工作，坚持要在华盛顿附近地区的社区学院继续担任教师。<ref name="nydn122808">{{cite news | url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/2008/12/27/2008-12-27_from_a_blind_date_to_second_lady_jill_bi.html?page=0 | title=From a blind date to second lady, Jill Biden's coming into her own | author=Evans, Heidi | newspaper=New York Daily News | date=2008-12-28 | accessdate=2009-01-03 | archive-date=2009-01-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090122021045/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/2008/12/27/2008-12-27_from_a_blind_date_to_second_lady_jill_bi.html?page=0 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="nyt112108">{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/23/fashion/23biden.html |title='Amtrak Joe' No More |author=Bosman, Julie |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2008-11-21 |accessdate=2008-11-25 |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129044229/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/23/fashion/23biden.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/reliable-source/2009/01/campuses_crusade_to_secure_pro.html |title=Campuses Crusade to Secure Prof. Biden |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=2009-01-16 |accessdate=2009-01-16 |archive-date=2012-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120323151809/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/reliable-source/2009/01/campuses_crusade_to_secure_pro.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>2009年1月，吉尔开始在全美第二大社区学院{{link-en|北弗吉尼亚社区学院|Northern Virginia Community College}}的[[亚历山德里亚_(弗吉尼亚州)|亚历山德里亚]]校区担任[[讲座教授|讲座教授]]，负责两门英文课程的教学工作。<ref name="lat020209"/><ref name="wapo012709">{{cite news | url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2009/01/27/jill_biden_returns_to_the_clas.html?hpid=news-col-blog | title=Jill Biden Returns to the Classroom | author=Rucker, Philip | newspaper=The Washington Post | date=2009-01-27 | accessdate=2009-01-27 | archive-date=2009-02-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090202112434/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2009/01/27/jill_biden_returns_to_the_clas.html?hpid=news-col-blog | dead-url=no }}</ref>美国历史上，在丈夫任职副总统期间仍保留自己工作的第二夫人已是少数，<ref name="pol112708" /><ref name="nyt112108" />而吉尔更是成为第一位在丈夫任职期间仍然保留自己有薪水的工作的第二夫人。<ref name="lat020209">{{cite news | url=http://www.latimes.com/news/politics/la-na-dr-jill-biden2-2009feb02,0,7421785.story | title=Jill Biden, doctor of education, is back in class | author=Abcarian, Robin | newspaper=Los Angeles Times | date=2009-02-02 | accessdate=2009-02-02 | archive-date=2009-02-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090203221226/http://www.latimes.com/news/politics/la-na-dr-jill-biden2-2009feb02,0,7421785.story | dead-url=no }}</ref>吉尔希望向公众推广社区学院教育，并为奥巴马总统的相关政策提出建议。<ref name="wapo012709"/>[[白宫|白宫]]在一般情况下遵从她本人的意愿，称呼她为“吉尔·拜登博士”（{{lang|en|"Dr. Jill Biden"}}）。<ref name="lat020209" /><ref name="pol061209">{{cite news | url=http://www.politico.com/news/stories/0609/23663.html | title=Dr. Jill Biden's public debut | author=Lee, Carol E. | newspaper=The Politico | date=2009-06-12 | accessdate=2014-02-10 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120921091828/http://www.politico.com/news/stories/0609/23663.html | archivedate=2012-09-21 | deadurl=no }}</ref>

吉尔任第二夫人期间任命前[[美国参议院外交委员会|参议院外交委员会]]顾问凯瑟琳·拉塞尔（{{lang|en|Catherine Russell}}）为自己的幕僚长；<ref>{{cite news | url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2008/11/biden-beefs-up-staff.html | title=Biden Beefs Up Staff | author=Rucker, Philip | newspaper=The Washington Post | accessdate=2014-02-10 | date=2008-11-25 | archive-date=2020-10-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017054055/http://voices.washingtonpost.com/44/2008/11/biden-beefs-up-staff.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>通信主管一职由[[霍华德·迪恩|霍华德·迪恩]]和[[伊丽莎白·爱德华兹|伊丽莎白·爱德华兹]]的前发言人柯特妮·奥唐纳（{{lang|en|Courtney O’Donnell}}）担任；<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/courtney-odonnell/gIQAMxY09O_topic.html | title=Courtney ODonnell, Communications Director for the Second Lady (since January 2009) | publisher=The Washington Post | accessdate=2014-02-09 | archive-date=2020-06-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605041222/https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/courtney-odonnell/gIQAMxY09O_topic.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>而她的政策主管则是{{link-en|摩根路易斯律师事务所|Morgan, Lewis & Bockius}}[[律师|律师]]克斯汀·怀特（{{lang|en|Kirsten White}}）。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/politics/vice-president-biden-announces-key-staff-appointments_100170407.html | title=Vice President Biden announces key staff appointments | agency=BNO News | publisher=Thaindian News | date=2009-03-24 | accessdate=2009-03-31 | archive-date=2009-03-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090327135410/http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/politics/vice-president-biden-announces-key-staff-appointments_100170407.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>身为第二夫人的吉尔旗下拥有一个八人团队协助其工作，而且在{{link-en|艾森豪威尔行政办公楼|Eisenhower Executive Office Building}}拥有一间角落套房。<ref name="pol061209"/>

[[File:US_Army_51255_Jill_Biden_visits_Guard_Soldiers.jpg|thumb]]军官会面]]
[[File:Michelle_Obama_and_Jill_Biden_in_Haiti_2010.jpg|thumb]]三个月之后，吉尔·拜登和米歇尔·奥巴马在[[海地|海地]][[第一夫人|第一夫人]]{{link-en|伊丽莎白·普雷瓦尔|Elisabeth Delatour Préval}}的陪同下访问海地首都[[太子港|太子港]]]]
[[2009年美國總統就職禮|2009年总统就职典礼]]前，吉尔参加了[[脱口秀|脱口秀]]节目《[[奥普拉·温弗里秀|-{zh-cn:奥普拉·温弗里秀;zh-hk:奧花·雲費秀;zh-tw:歐普拉·溫芙蕾秀;}-]]》。她在节目中表示贝拉克·奥巴马曾向其夫乔·拜登提供两个职位进行选择：副总统或[[美国国务卿|国务卿]]。<ref name="slip">{{Cite news|url=http://www.startribune.com/politics/national/37849314.html?elr=KArksLckD8EQDUoaEyqyP4O:DW3ckUiD3aPc:_Yyc:aUnciaec8O7EyUsI|title=Jill Biden lets slip secret about Joe|accessdate=2009-01-20|location=Minneapolis|newspaper=Star Tribune|date=2009-01-19|archive-date=2014-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221231356/http://www.startribune.com/politics/national/37849314.html?elr=KArksLckD8EQDUoaEyqyP4O:DW3ckUiD3aPc:_Yyc:aUnciaec8O7EyUsI|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyt011909">{{cite news | url=http://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/19/the-bidens-on-oprah/ | title=The Bidens on Oprah | author=Seelye, Katharine Q. | newspaper=The New York Times | date=2009-02-19 | accessdate=2009-01-20 | archive-date=2020-06-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605041213/https://thecaucus.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/19/the-bidens-on-oprah/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>但此前乔·拜登的发言人曾表示，奥巴马只向他提供了副总统这一个职位。<ref name="nyt011909"/>2009年5月，奥巴马总统宣布将由吉尔负责主管一个倡议行动，行动旨在提高公众对社区学院教育价值的重视。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iGr8abuzwYYWi91x-7O68TzBVXjQ |title=Obama says job losses sobering, but sees progress |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=2009-05-08 |accessdate=2009-05-18 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101230103607/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iGr8abuzwYYWi91x-7O68TzBVXjQ |archivedate=2010-12-30 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

2009年6月，吉尔在纽约市[[布鲁克林区|布鲁克林区]]{{link-en|国王区社区学院|Kingsborough Community College}}毕业典礼上演讲，<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/2009/06/12/2009-06-12_second_lady_jill_biden_captivates_kingsborough_community_college_students.html | title=Second Lady Jill Biden captivates Kingsborough Community College students | author=Saltonstall, David | newspaper=New York Daily News | date=2009-06-12 | accessdate=2009-06-16 | archive-date=2009-06-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090615052221/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/politics/2009/06/12/2009-06-12_second_lady_jill_biden_captivates_kingsborough_community_college_students.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>并获得[[纽约城市大学|纽约城市大学]]的[[名誉学位|名誉]][[文学博士|文学博士]]学位。<ref>{{cite press release |title=Dr. Jill Biden to Deliver Commencement Address at Kingsborough Community College |url=http://news.prnewswire.com/DisplayReleaseContent.aspx?ACCT=104&STORY=/www/story/06-04-2009/0005038635&EDATE= |publisher=PRNewswire |date=2009-06-04 |accessdate=2009-06-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090522040604/http://news.prnewswire.com/DisplayReleaseContent.aspx?ACCT=104 |archivedate=2009-05-22 }}</ref>2009年秋季学期，吉尔继续在北弗吉尼亚社区学院教授两门英文阅读和写作课程。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.politicsdaily.com/2009/09/03/jill-biden-captain-of-the-vice-squad |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090923233637/http://www.politicsdaily.com/2009/09/03/jill-biden-captain-of-the-vice-squad |archivedate=2009-09-23 |title=Jill Biden, Captain of the Vice Squad |author=Sweet, Lynn |publisher=Politics Daily |date=2009-09-03 |accessdate=2009-09-08 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>2010年1月，她在特拉华大学毕业典礼上进行演讲，这是她首次在主要大学进行类似演讲。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.wboc.com/Global/story.asp?S=11795605 | title=Jill Biden Speaks to UD Grads | agency=Associated Press | publisher=WBOC-TV | date=2010-01-09 | accessdate=2010-01-17 | archive-date=2012-02-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120222052026/http://www.wboc.com/Global/story.asp?S=11795605 | dead-url=no }}</ref>2010年8月，吉尔在{{Link-en|Lifetime电视台|Lifetime (TV network)}}电视剧《{{link-en|军嫂 (电视剧)|Army Wives|军嫂}}》的一集中以自己的真实身份[[友情客串|客串]]出镜，这也是她关注军人家庭的公益活动的一部分。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://abcnews.go.com/GMA/jill-biden-military-families/story?id=11335486 | title=Second Lady Jill Biden's Acting Debut to Help Military Families | author=Wlach, Jen | author2=Ferran, Lee | work=Good Morning America | publisher=ABC News | date=2010-08-06 | accessdate=2010-08-09 | archive-date=2020-06-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605041233/https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/jill-biden-military-families/story?id=11335486 | dead-url=no }}</ref>2011年4月，她和米歇尔·奥巴马一同发起了全国性的倡议行动“支持军队”（{{lang|en|Joining Forces}}），对美国军人家庭的需求以及面临的困境进行宣传，并对其提供支持和帮助。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2011/04/michelle-obama-jill-biden-celebrities-highlight-the-needs-of-military-families.html |title=Michelle Obama, Jill Biden & Celebrities Highlight the Needs of Military Families |author=Bradley, Tahman |work=Political Punch |publisher=ABC News |date=2011-04-09 |accessdate=2011-04-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110410192126/http://blogs.abcnews.com/politicalpunch/2011/04/michelle-obama-jill-biden-celebrities-highlight-the-needs-of-military-families.html |archivedate=2011-04-10 }}</ref>2011年9月，吉尔对[[美国国际开发署|美国国际开发署]]的FWD行动（{{lang|en|"FWD campaign"}}，"FWD"是{{lang|en|"Famine, War, and Drought"}}的缩写，意为“饥荒、战争和干旱”）提供支持和帮助。该行动旨在提升社会对[[非洲之角|非洲之角]]地区的饥荒、战争和干旱的认识，并对该地区生存状况因此受到影响的超过1300万人口提供援助。<ref>{{cite press release | url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/dr-jill-biden-joins-usaid-and-ad-council-to-debut-fwd-campaign-for-the-crisis-in-the-horn-of-africa-132605078.html | title=Dr. Jill Biden Joins USAID and Ad Council to Debut FWD Campaign for the Crisis in the Horn of Africa | publisher=PR Newswire | date=2011-10-26 | access-date=2014-02-10 | archive-date=2012-07-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120713200627/http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/dr-jill-biden-joins-usaid-and-ad-council-to-debut-fwd-campaign-for-the-crisis-in-the-horn-of-africa-132605078.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

此时她仍然继续在北弗吉尼亚社区学院任教，<ref>{{cite magazine | url=http://thepage.time.com/2011/03/22/biden-visits-japanese-embassy/ | title=Biden Visits Japanese Embassy | magazine=Time | date=2011-03-22 | accessdate=2011-04-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110504132718/http://thepage.time.com/2011/03/22/biden-visits-japanese-embassy/ | archive-date=2011-05-04 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>并在2011年获得了终身[[教授|副教授]]的职位。她在此时负责三门英文和写作课程，每周上课两天。<ref name="pol-regular">{{cite news | url=http://www.politico.com/news/stories/0611/57887.html | title=Joe and Jill Biden's 'regular' lives | author=Parnes, Amie | newspaper=Politico | date=2011-06-28 | accessdate=2011-06-28 | archive-date=2011-06-30 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110630014939/http://www.politico.com/news/stories/0611/57887.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>吉尔的这个职位是其正常能力所足以获得的。在学校，她和其他教师共用橱柜，也坚持与学生见面的正常办公时间，并要求负责其安保工作的[[美国特勤局|特勤人员]]尽量身着不起眼的便服。<ref name="pol-regular"/>她和丈夫在官邸内的生活主要是围绕自己的家庭和住在附近的孙辈。<ref name="pol-regular"/>2012年6月，她出版了一本儿童图书《不要忘记，上帝保佑我们的军队》（{{lang|en|''Don't Forget, God Bless Our Troops''}}），图书主要内容是关于自己继子在军中服役的生活。<ref name="pol-2012"/>
