=== 第二任期 ===
[[File:Joe_and_Jill_Biden_in_the_inaugural_parade_2013.jpg|thumb]]参加{{link-en|2013年美国总统就职礼|Second inauguration of Barack Obama|奥巴马总统第二次就职典礼}}的游行]]

[[2012年美国总统选举|2012年总统选举]]中，乔·拜登参选连任副总统。吉尔在这次竞选活动中行动低调，<ref name="pol-2012">{{cite news |url=http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1012/81877.html |title=Jill Biden tiptoes into 2012 election |author=Slack, Donovan |newspaper=Politico |date=2012-10-01 |accessdate=2014-02-10 |archive-date=2015-05-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150529131425/http://www.politico.com/news/stories/1012/81877.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>她照常进行平日的教学工作，仅出席了几场竞选活动。<ref name="pol-2012"/>尽管奥巴马的竞选团队将她视为争取军人家庭、教师和女性选民的重要人物，但吉尔对政治和公众演讲并无兴趣。<ref name="pol-2012"/>2012年11月6日，奥巴马和乔·拜登成功连任。2013年1月，吉尔身着[[王薇薇|王薇薇]]设计的蓝色丝绸礼服参加了总统就职典礼舞会。其作为美国第二夫人的第二任期也正式开始。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2266156/Inauguration-2013-party-Obama-Ushers-Gangnam-Style-dance-Michelle-grooves-Beyonce.html | title=Inside the White House after-party: How the President took part in a Gangnam Style dance off and Michelle grooved to 'Single Ladies' at celebrity-packed bash | author=Boyle, Louise | author2=Warren, Lydia | newspaper=Daily Mail | date=2013-01-23 | accessdate=2014-02-10 | archive-date=2020-10-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027011352/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2266156/Inauguration-2013-party-Obama-Ushers-Gangnam-Style-dance-Michelle-grooves-Beyonce.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[File:Vice_President_Joe_Biden_and_his_wife_Dr._Jill_Biden_award_gold_medals_to_the_U.S._Invictus_wheelchair_rugby_team_at_the_2016_Invictus_Games_(26896635511).jpg|thumb]]
在第二任期中，吉尔继续参与各种支持老兵的活动，曾多次到访截肢和烧伤病患康复机构“无畏中心”（{{lang|en|Center for the Intrepid}}）<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.defense.gov/news/newsarticle.aspx?id=123474 | title=Dr. Biden Thanks Wounded Troops, Caregivers in San Antonio | first=Elaine | last=Sanchez | publisher=U.S. Department of Defense | date=2014-10-23 | accessdate=2016-01-22 | archive-date=2014-11-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108140811/http://www.defense.gov/news/newsarticle.aspx?id=123474 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，还与米歇尔·奥巴马共同参加了英国为伤残军人举办的“{{le|不可征服运动会|Invictus Games}}”的推广活动。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/prince-harry-joins-michelle-obama-and-jill-biden-to-promote-invictus-games/|title=Prince Harry, Michelle Obama team up to promote Invictus Games|work=CBS|date=2015-10-28|accessdate=2016-01-22|archive-date=2020-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200912164253/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/prince-harry-joins-michelle-obama-and-jill-biden-to-promote-invictus-games/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[2014年美国中期选举|2014年美国中期选举]]期间，吉尔曾为多名民主党议员助选，包括[[科罗拉多州|科罗拉多州]]的[[马克·尤德尔|马克·尤德尔]]和[[乔治亚州|乔治亚州]]的{{le|米歇尔·纳恩|Michelle Nunn}}等重要选战候选人。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.nbc11news.com/home/headlines/Jill-Biden-tries-to-fire-up-Democrats-for-Udall-281186061.html | title=Jill Biden tries to fire up Democrats for Udall | agency=Associated Press | publisher=KKCO | date=2014-11-01 | accessdate=2018-05-27 | archive-date=2020-06-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605041319/https://www.nbc11news.com/home/headlines/Jill-Biden-tries-to-fire-up-Democrats-for-Udall-281186061.html | dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://politics.blog.ajc.com/2014/10/16/jill-biden-to-raise-money-for-campaign-with-michelle-nunn/ | title=Jill Biden to raise money for, campaign with Michelle Nunn | first=Daniel | last=Malloy | newspaper=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution | date=2014-10-16 | accessdate=2016-01-22 | archive-date=2014-11-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108142244/http://politics.blog.ajc.com/2014/10/16/jill-biden-to-raise-money-for-campaign-with-michelle-nunn/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

2015年5月30日，乔·拜登的长子[[博·拜登|博·拜登]]因[[脑癌|脑癌]]逝世<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/31/us/politics/joseph-r-biden-iii-vice-presidents-son-beau-dies-at-46.html|title = Beau Biden, Vice President Joe Biden’s Son, Dies at 46|last = Shear|first = Michael D.|date = 2015-05-30|work = New York Times|accessdate = 2016-01-22|archive-date = 2016-01-15|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160115135616/http://www.nytimes.com/2015/05/31/us/politics/joseph-r-biden-iii-vice-presidents-son-beau-dies-at-46.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>，之后乔·拜登和吉尔两人长时间无法走出丧子之痛。<ref name="Politico">{{cite web|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2015/09/biden-jill-joe-2016-elections-213428|title=Jill's dilemma|work=Politico|date=2015-09-09|accessdate=2016-01-22|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108111752/https://www.politico.com/story/2015/09/biden-jill-joe-2016-elections-213428|dead-url=no}}</ref>受此影响，乔·拜登在长时间考虑后决定不参加[[2016年美国总统选举|2016年美国总统选举]]。10月21日，吉尔陪同乔·拜登在[[白宫玫瑰园|白宫玫瑰园]]发表声明，将这一决定告知公众。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aol.com/article/2015/10/21/biden-announces-hes-not-running-for-president/21252056/?icid=maing-grid7%7Chtmlws-main-bb%7Cdl1%7Csec1_lnk3%26pLid%3D36905727|title=Biden says he will not seek 2016 Democratic nomination|publisher=Thomson Reuters|first=Jeff|last=Mason|date=2015-10-21|accessdate=2016-01-22|archive-date=2015-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123032850/http://www.aol.com/article/2015/10/21/biden-announces-hes-not-running-for-president/21252056/?icid=maing-grid7%7Chtmlws-main-bb%7Cdl1%7Csec1_lnk3%26pLid%3D36905727|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Comment  Joe Biden Is Not Running For President In 2016|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/joe-biden-president-2016_55f1cefbe4b093be51be0d69|publisher=Huffington Post|accessdate=2015-11-22|archive-date=2016-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160103000202/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/joe-biden-president-2016_55f1cefbe4b093be51be0d69|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Joe Biden Decides Not to Enter Presidential Race|url=http://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-biden-decides-not-to-enter-presidential-race-1445444657|publisher=The Wall Street Journal|accessdate=2015-11-22|archive-date=2021-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210103083107/https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-biden-decides-not-to-enter-presidential-race-1445444657|dead-url=no}}</ref>但吉尔本人并不赞同乔·拜登的这一决定，她事实上非常希望丈夫参选，认为他有能力有资格，并且会成为“最优秀的总统”。<ref name="Politico"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/joe-biden-campaign-60-minutes_562cf4bce4b0ec0a3894bedf|title=Jill Biden Says She Was Disappointed That Joe Didn't Run|date=2015-10-25|first=Sam|last=Stein|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=2015-11-22|archive-date=2015-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151123043218/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/joe-biden-campaign-60-minutes_562cf4bce4b0ec0a3894bedf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="today">{{cite news|url=http://www.today.com/news/jill-biden-america-missed-opportunity-when-joe-didn-t-run-t86526|title=Jill Biden: 'America missed an opportunity' when Joe didn't run for president|publisher=Today|date=2016-04-15|accessdate=2017-01-21|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030064516/https://www.today.com/news/jill-biden-america-missed-opportunity-when-joe-didn-t-run-t86526|dead-url=no}}</ref>

