== 2020年总统竞选活动 ==
{{main|喬·拜登2020年美國總統競選}}
[[File:Jill_Biden_(48537868461).jpg|thumb]]
就在大家纷纷讨论乔参选[[2020年美国总统选举|2020年美国总统选举]]的可能性时，吉尔成了乔做决定的重要人物<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/national-international/Biden-Campaign-Fundraising-Challenge-506921771.html | title=Biden Eyes Fundraising Challenge Amid New Sense of Urgency | first1=Steve | last1=Peoples | first2=Julie | last2=Pace | publisher=WNBC-TV | date=2019-03-09 | access-date=2019-03-09 | archive-date=2019-04-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190406015556/https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/national-international/Biden-Campaign-Fundraising-Challenge-506921771.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。到2019年3月接受访问时，吉尔表示“踊跃”支持他参选<ref>{{cite news | title=Plan in Place, Biden's Army Awaits Biden | first1=Jonathan | last1=Martin | first2=Alexander | last2=Burns | newspaper=The New York Times | date=2019-03-08 | page=A1}}</ref>。

[[喬·拜登2020年美國總統競選|喬·拜登2020年美國總統競選]]活动于2019年4月25日正式宣布，《{{tsl|en|Town & Country (magazine)|小镇小村}}》杂志的封面内容宣称“吉尔·拜登或许是乔·拜登最重要的政治资产”<ref name="tc2020">{{cite magazine | url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/politics/a26944878/jill-biden-joe-biden-wife-facts/ | title=Why Jill Biden Might Just Be Joe Biden's Greatest Political Asset | first=Maggie | last=Maloney | date=2019-04-25 | magazine=Town and Country | access-date=2019-04-27 | archive-date=2019-04-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425153716/https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/politics/a26944878/jill-biden-joe-biden-wife-facts/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

几天后，吉尔就多位女性指责她丈夫涉嫌性骚扰的事件发表讲话。她表示：“我认为你们并不知道究竟有多少人接近拜登，他们有男有女，都是来找同情和安慰的。但说直白点，我认为他必须要准确判断人们接近他的时机，以及他将会作出的反应。他也许不应该接触他们<ref name="abc-touch">{{cite news | url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/joe-jill-biden-respond-women-made-uncomfortable/story?id=62665123 | title=Joe and Jill Biden respond to women who say he made them uncomfortable | first=Molly | last=Nagle | publisher=ABC News | date=2019-04-30 | access-date=2019-05-03 | archive-date=2019-05-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502142644/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/joe-jill-biden-respond-women-made-uncomfortable/story?id=62665123 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。”她又表示自己之前也经历过被男人闯入私人空间的事情，“我就走到一边，没有直接把事情挑明......情况会改变的。那可是女性不敢發聲的时代。我清楚记得那是一次工作的面试......如果这样的事情发生在今天，我会转过身，说‘你究竟想干什么？’......情况就完全不同了<ref name="abc-touch" />。”值得注意的是，在提到乔于1991年{{le|安妮塔·希尔|Anita Hill}}事件及{{le|克拉伦斯·托马斯最高法院大法官提名|Clarence Thomas Supreme Court nomination}}中的角色时，她表示“应该放眼未来”<ref name="npr-time">{{cite news | url=https://www.npr.org/2019/05/07/720696969/jill-biden-says-it-s-time-to-move-on-from-anita-hill-controversy | title=Jill Biden Says 'It's Time To Move On' From Anita Hill Controversy | author-first=Danielle | author-last=Kurtzleben | publisher=NPR | date=2019-05-07 | access-date=2020-02-12 | archive-date=2020-02-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202022806/https://www.npr.org/2019/05/07/720696969/jill-biden-says-it-s-time-to-move-on-from-anita-hill-controversy | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

